</use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525716\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525716\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 14, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ajc1665702551017.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ajc1665702551017.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ajc1665702551017.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ajc1665702551017\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To create IncludeScripts, Global ProcScripts, and snippets for use during modeling and\n      construction, you use the Project Editor.</p>\n<section class=\"section prereq\" id=\"ajc1665702551017__prereq_sgk_2bf_jzb\"><span class=\"tasklabel\"><b class=\"sectiontitle tasklabel\">Before you begin: </b></span>You must have created a project to contain your application\n         definitions. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>.</section>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"ajc1665702551017__context_w8943ab1b5b3_w8944ab1b5_w8945ab1\">For other types of objects, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ita1705565048634.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ita1705565048634.html\" title=\"To create libraries of modeled properties, global objects, and language setups, use the editors available in the More Editors menu.\">Create a Library for Modeled Properties or Global Objects</a>.<p class=\"p\" id=\"ajc1665702551017__p_d3983e1_d3984e1_d3985e1\">To create\n            IncludeScripts, Global ProcScripts, and snippets for use during modeling and\n            construction:</p></section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ajc1665702551017__li_d1490e1_d1491e1_d1492e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Open your project. In the U-Bar, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Browse</span>, select\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">prj</code>, then choose the project you want to open.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ajc1665702551017__li_d1493e1_d1494e1_d1495e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Templates</span> tab of the Resource Browser, select the\n               desired library template.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ajc1665702551017__li_d1496e1_d1497e1_d1498e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Drag and drop it onto the project in the Structure Editor.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ajc1665702551017__li_d1499e1_d1500e1_d1501e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Rename the library.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ajc1665702551017__li_d1502e1_d1503e1_d1504e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally, edit the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Description</span> property to provide a more\n               informative description.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ajc1665702551017__li_d1505e1_d1506e1_d1507e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To open the library, right-click it and choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Open</span> from the\n               menu.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"ajc1665702551017__li_d1508e1_d1509e1_d1510e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the library editor, drag templates from the Resource Browser and drop them onto\n               the library object in the Structure to create them. Then edit them as required,\n               depending on the object.</span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Working with Projects</a><p>Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kee1692183917031.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Libraries</a><p>Libraries are collections of objects that can be shared in some way, either during development, or at runtime. They are main development objects, so whenever they are saved or exported, all the objects that they contain are included.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eew1665702619155.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Naming Rules for Uniface Development Objects</a><p>The name of a development object is its unique identifier. When naming development objects, use the allowed syntax for the object name. Avoid using words that are reserved for use within Uniface and your own environment, including the operating system and database.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525716\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525716\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Create a Library Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 14, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 To create IncludeScripts, Global ProcScripts, and snippets for use during modeling and construction, you use the Project Editor. Before you begin: You must have created a project to contain your application definitions. For more information, see Working with Projects . For other types of objects, see Create a Library for Modeled Properties or Global Objects . To create IncludeScripts, Global ProcScripts, and snippets for use during modeling and construction: Open your project. In the U-Bar, click Browse , select prj , then choose the project you want to open. In the Templates tab of the Resource Browser, select the desired library template. Drag and drop it onto the project in the Structure Editor. Rename the library. Optionally, edit the Description property to provide a more informative description. To open the library, right-click it and choose Open from the menu. In the library editor, drag templates from the Resource Browser and drop them onto the library object in the Structure to create them. Then edit them as required, depending on the object. Related Links Working with Projects Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions. Libraries Libraries are collections of objects that can be shared in some way, either during development, or at runtime. They are main development objects, so whenever they are saved or exported, all the objects that they contain are included. Naming Rules for Uniface Development Objects The name of a development object is its unique identifier. When naming development objects, use the allowed syntax for the object name. Avoid using words that are reserved for use within Uniface and your own environment, including the operating system and database. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}